SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYTuesday 7 June S10 V1 Germany and England resume a rivalry that has proven intense and closely fought over the decades when they meet in Munich in the Nations League on Tuesday. More details at www.soccer6.co.za M1 Cape Verde Islands vs Togo: Cape Verde lost their opening Cup of Nations qualifier on Friday to Burkina Faso while Togo were held to a 2-2 draw at home by Eswatini.M2 Finland vs Montenegro: Finland are without success in their past five home matches. Montenegro began their Nations League campaign with a 2-0 home win over Romania at the weekend.M3 Zambia vs Comoros Islands: Zambia have won both previous meetings against the islanders, who were one of the surprise packages at the last Cup of Nations finals in Cameroon at the start of the year.M4 United Arab Emirates vs Australia: Asian zone playoff match in Doha to determine which Asian country goes through to the inter-continental playoff against Peru to determine a place at the World Cup finals.M5 Bosnia-Herzegovina vs Romania: Bosnia drew at Finland in their first Nations League game on Saturday but Romania suffered a 2-0 loss at Montenegro at the same time.M6 Faroe Islands vs Luxembourg: The Faroes have won once of their past seven matches. Luxembourg registered a 2-0 away win at Lithuania on Saturday.M7 Germany vs England: The English are narrowly 14-13 ahead in the win count of previous clashes between the two countries with only six draws.M8 Italy vs Hungary: Italy have won only one of their past six matches while Hungary scored a first win in six decades over England on Saturday.M9 Cuiaba vs Corinthians: Three successive defeats as meant Cuiaba dropping into the relegation zone in Brazil. Corinthians won away at Atletico Goianense on Saturday to end a run of four 1-1 draws in a row.M10 Gremio vs Novorizontino: Gremio have played three successive goalless draws. Two of Novorizontino previous three games also ended 0-0. Suggested permutation:R8.00 1 x 1 x 1 x 3 x 1,2 x 2,3 x 1 x 1 x 3 x 1